---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - Dhwani">
  <main>
    <article class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20 px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-12 max-w-[1100px] mx-auto">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-[clamp(2.5rem,7vw,4.5rem)] font-semibold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.025em] text-ink mb-10 md:mb-12">
        About Dhwani
      </h1>

      <div class="prose-content space-y-7 md:space-y-8">
        <p class="font-serif-body text-[1rem] md:text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] md:leading-[1.85] text-ink-light font-light">
          A curated directory dedicated to organizing and celebrating India's rich literary heritage.
        </p>

        <p class="font-serif-body text-[1rem] md:text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] md:leading-[1.85] text-ink-light font-light">
          Dhwani gathers links to thousands of public domain literary works—from ancient Vedic hymns to modern poetry—making them discoverable and accessible to readers worldwide. Our collection spans multiple languages, genres, and centuries, offering a comprehensive guide to Indian literary tradition.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-[1.65rem] md:text-[2rem] font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink mt-12 md:mt-14 mb-6 md:mb-7">
          Our Mission
        </h2>

        <p class="font-serif-body text-[1rem] md:text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] md:leading-[1.85] text-ink-light font-light">
          We believe that India's literary heritage belongs to everyone. By gathering and organizing links to these works in one place, we ensure they remain discoverable and accessible for future generations. Every text, poem, and philosophical treatise tells a story—of human experience, cultural evolution, and timeless wisdom.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-[1.65rem] md:text-[2rem] font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink mt-12 md:mt-14 mb-6 md:mb-7">
          What We Offer
        </h2>

        <ul class="space-y-2.5 md:space-y-3 font-serif-body text-[0.95rem] md:text-[1.05rem] leading-[1.7] md:leading-[1.8] text-ink-light font-light">
          <li>Curated collections organized by era, language, and theme</li>
          <li>Full-text search across thousands of works</li>
          <li>Works sourced from Project Gutenberg, Internet Archive, and other open repositories</li>
          <li>Clean, distraction-free reading experience</li>
          <li>Historical context and literary analysis for each work</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-[1.65rem] md:text-[2rem] font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink mt-12 md:mt-14 mb-6 md:mb-7">
          Open & Free
        </h2>

        <p class="font-serif-body text-[1rem] md:text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] md:leading-[1.85] text-ink-light font-light">
          All works in our archive are in the public domain or available through open access licenses. Dhwani is built with open-source tools and will always remain free to use.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-12 md:mt-14 pt-7 md:pt-8 border-t border-line">
          <p class="font-serif-body text-sm text-ink-lighter font-light">
            For questions, suggestions, or contributions, reach out at{' '}
            <a href="mailto:hello@dhwani.org" class="text-accent hover:text-ink transition-colors">hello@dhwani.org</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
